    "summary": "I am a passionate physicist, with a strong drive to translate abstract ideas into everyday life applications. \n\nI have a solid background in optical spectroscopy of nanostructures, ranging from semiconductor self-assembled quantum dots, pyramidal quantum dots, colloidal quantum dots and two-dimensional materials. As a postdoctoral researcher, I worked in the field of cavity quantum electrodynamics with semiconductor exciton-polaritons. I am currently working in the field of quantum acoustic, where we generate and manipulate single phonons (quantum of mechanical vibrations) for on-chip quantum information processing.",
